===Noun===
{{en-noun|abdomens|abdomina}}

# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} The fat surrounding the belly. {{defdate|Attested from the mid 16<sup>th</sup> century until the late 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=3}}</ref>
# {{context|anatomy|lang=en}} The [[belly]], or that part of the body between the [[thorax]] and the [[pelvis]], not including the back; or in some lower vertebrates, the portion between the [[cardiac]] and [[caudal]] regions. {{defdate|First attested in the early 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|anatomy|lang=en}} The cavity of the belly, which is lined by the [[peritoneum]], and contains the [[viscera]]; often restricted in humans to the part between the [[diaphragm]] and the [[commencement]] of the pelvis, the [[remainder]] being called the [[pelvic cavity]]. {{defdate|First attested in the early 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: ''He was all bent over complaining of pains in the abdomen.''
# {{context|zoology|entomology|lang=en}} The [[posterior]] section of the body, behind the thorax, in insects, [[crustacean]]s, and other [[Arthropoda]]. {{defdate|First attested in the late 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>

